  "validityNotes": "AQ-10 was developed as a primary-care 'red flag' screener. Original sensitivity 0.88 and specificity 0.91 at the recommended cutoff of 6 (Allison et al. 2012). Replication studies have found lower sensitivity and specificity in some populations, particularly among women and gender-diverse adults. Treat scores as a prompt for further evaluation, not as a definitive indicator.",
